items.name: Sabrina Salerno (1988-95 era - CHECKPOINT)
items.description:
THERE IS A LORA VERSION OF THIS MODEL AVAILABLE. IT IS EXACTLY THE SAME MODEL AS THIS ONE, EXCEPT IN A DIFFERENT AND LIGHTER FORMAT.

Shivam Dreambooth of the 1980s Italian singer, model and actress, using 48 ref images and 1980 (real) reg images, for 8,000 steps

Keep the sampling steps for the initial images no higher than about 60-70, ideally on the good Karras interpreters, and keep working the picture until it assembles. You can move the steps up as you go in for detail later with inpainting, etc..

I generally use these models in complex workflows, inpainting faces after initial T2Is, and using ControlNet extensively. So if you're hoping for one-click prompt magic, my models aren't data-curated with this in mind, but rather as tools for traditional workflows that use Photoshop and other older methods.

This model may produce subject-accurate NSFW output unless countered by negative prompts.

items.name: 3_3 (Eye/Face expression) Chibi Lycoris
items.description:
3_3 (Eye/Face expression) Chibi LoRA

LoRA request queue on my discord: https://discord.gg/DAfjhRfyEM

This model was trained using 32 images of the expression. It was trained on the NAI model so it should work with most anime based models. Some of the images were also non-chibis, but I didn't get the eyes to generate on normal characters.

Recommended weight is between 0.9 and 1.

Trigger words are 3_3, chibi. Works with other character LoRA if they aren't too strong.

Example images were generated using JafaMix v4 with 30 steps, then hires. fixed by 1.5

The last one was gen'd with my human pom pom LoRA

Note: This was made exclusively on anime images and on an anime checkpoint. Feel free to post images on realistic, semirealistic etc. checkpoints, but do not rate it on that! This was made to be used on anime checkpoints so keep reviews for that!

items.name: Ulti [One Piece] Character LoRA
items.description:
Ulti from One Piece - Character LoRA

If you like what I create, feel free to support on Ko-Fi!üçµ

Make sure to leave a review if you like it, would love to see all the pictures everyone creates!

Trained on the NovelAI model, and tested with many different anime specific models. This LoRA definitely can produce images of Ulti from One Piece. However, you can also feel free to generate her in other outfits, such as a tank top and shorts in one of my example images. I found that this LoRA works well with a weight of 0.9 - 1. items.description:
Cyber Samurai - by HailoKnight

Hello!
Second LoRA is already here! Hope you enjoy it!

Things To know:

  • You should use the trigger word cybersamurai

  • Works with katanas and without. OBS. if you are going to generate pictures with katanas have patience!! Weapons a really cursed in Stable Diffusion, perfection does not come in 10-15 pictures, could do if your lucky ;)

  • This model is trained on ReV Animated, for best result, use that model!!

Usage Tips :

  • The LoRA weight I have been using is 1, but feel free to try and experiment!

  • I usually use the sampler DPM++ 2M Karras with 36 steps, for best result generate 1024*1024 or use the Hires. fix

  • Example promt for the picture can be found on the uploaded pictures for the LoRA!

Hope you enjoy! Feel free to upload and share all your amazing creations!
